% Folder displayTools%% This directory contains the main mFiles for exptTools experiment types%  1. They define the basic data structures used in exptTools %     for different types of experiments (staircases, scans, trials, etc)%  2. They define the functions for presenting the stimuli and running%     the experiment (scans, staircases, etc)%% Contents:%% addTrialEvent.m% clickMouse2Begin.m% countDown.m% createStimulusStruct.m% dispStringInCenter.m% dispStringInCenterFast.m% doScan.m% doTrial.m% pressKey2Begin.m% showStimulus.m% standardYNfeedback.m% testTiming.m% waitTill.m%%%% ееее NOTE: The structure descriptions below need to be updated.  (WAP, BTB, 10-18-98)%% This directory contains the main mFiles for exptTools experiment types%  1. They define the basic data structures used in exptTools %     for different types of experiments (staircases, scans, trials, etc)%  2. They define the functions for presenting the stimuli and running%     the experiment (scans, staircases, etc)% Below is a description of the basic few structures that currently exist.%% Stimulus structure:% to create a stimulus, see createStimulusStruct.m% to display a stimulus, see showStimulus.m% stimulus =%                 image: [ 73x121  uint8 ]%                  cmap: [256x3x37 uint8 ]%                   seq: [  1x38   double]%              imagePtr: 39119616% % % Trial structure:	%  Used extensively in staircases and scans% trial =	% 			stimulus: [1x2 struct]%                  ISI: 0.1000%     responseInterval: NaN	%         ISIstimulus:% 		% 		% Ballistic scan structure:% used for simple scans in which two stimuli are repeatedly shown% for some period of time (18 secs, for example) in alternation.% scan =%      stimulus1: struct% 	 stimulus2: struct%      nCycles: 6% 	 dispString: 'name of experiment'% % 			   % Scan structure:% More complex structure that allows trials and responses during scans% scan =%              trial: [1x2  struct]%     trialNumberSeq: [1 1 1 1 1 1 2 2 1 1 1 1 1 1 2 2 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 1]%       		   ITI: 2% % % Staircase structure:% staircase = %             stimulus: [1xn  struct] if n>1, n should be numInterleaves*numTrials, for % 								   psuedorandomization or predetermination of stimuli.%           						   if n=1 then all trials are the same (except for intensity).%                  ISI: double      interstimulus interval (secs)%     responseInterval: double      (secs) NaN waits for user to respond%       numInterleaves: integer     number of interleaved staircases%            numTrials: integer     number of trials for each staircase%              logFlag: boolean     1 for stepping in log increments/decrements.%       intensityRange: 1x2 double  range of intensity values%    numIntensitySteps: double      number of steps in intensityRange.  (see logFlag)%        testIntensity: double      intensity of test stimulus%                nDown: integer     number of correct responses in a row before decreasing intensity (3)%  			     nUp: integer     number of incorrect responses in a row before increasing intensity (1)%         stimFunction: string      name of function to call to change intensity range.%        stimFieldName: string      name of field of stimulus that's linked to intensity% 